Description:
QUAINT COTTAGE OPPOSITE FORESHORE!
Charming 2 bedroom cedar cottage on attractive treed block approx.. 620 sq.m. Featuring living/ dining area with wood and gas heating, separate cosy kitchen, timber look vinyl flooring, bathroom and laundry combined, veranda along front, back veranda, single garage and the property is fully fenced. Situated in a secluded and tranquil setting with beach track nearly at door. Perfect for peaceful getaway, investment or first home buyers. Minutes to small group of shops including doctor, chemist, bank, ambulance depot and cafes, wineries and tourist attractions. Phillip Island and major shopping centre within 25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
Prized Position on 1069sqm!
This one is a catch - with a tidy 3 bedroom, 1 bathroom home, a huge 1069sqm (approx.) block perfect for subdivision (STCA), heaps of car storage, a huge shed and separate studio this one has everything.
The home is neat and simple with beautiful timber-look floors, large open plan kitchen with Smeg cooking appliances, and dishwasher. It boasts plenty of bench space and plentiful cabinetry all overlooking a sizable dining and living area. The master bedroom is complemented by a walk-in robe with remaining 2 bedrooms having built-in robes. All are serviced by a central, family bathroom with corner spa bath.
Outside is a great outdoor entertaining area, a single garage has been converted into a storage room but could easily be used as a 4th bedroom, man cave or outdoor/indoor entertaining space. With a double carport on one side of the home and a HUGE possibly 6 car carport on the other car storage will certainly not be a problem. A good sized back yard, with a double garage and separate studio perfect for use as a home office or salon is also included.
Other notable features include: 5.1kw 20 panel solar system, separate solar hot water, and water tank.
Walking distance to shops, Lang Lang Primary School and public transport this one is perfect for subdivision and has had prior council approval for 3 units.

Description:
STROLL TO CAFES & FORESHORE!!!
If you are in the market to purchase a building block in Coronet Bay you would realise that there are not many that come on the market. This block is affordable and ideally located within walking distance to a safe sandy swimming beach, playground and shop. Coronet Bay is a popular beach for families and people come from all around to enjoy the atmosphere on New Years Eve and fireworks. Bring the boat as there is a 24 hour boat ramp only a few minutes away.
Local group of shops which include doctor , chemist, bank and cafes are 7 minutes away and major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins. Easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.
This land can also be viewed on www.yourlandshop.com.au

Description:
Modern Family Home
This quality built home 26sq URL BV home on approx. 739m2 block. Spacious master bedroom with his & hers walk in robe and built in drawers. Ensuite has double vanity and shower.
Study has built in full length desk with book shelf. Second & third bedrooms with robes. Second bathroom with shower, vanity and bath.
Floating timer floors in hall, entrance, kitchen and family room with a split system air con. Separate lounge with plantation shutters, huge family room with double doors out to alfresco area, also has built in cupboards.
Beautiful kitchen with walk in pantry, island bench, dishwasher, pot draws, 900mm wide gas cook top and stove, with electric oven. Large bench space.
Side gate access to back yard. 18 solar panels 4.5kw, veggie patch and sandpit. Double garage URL remote, garden shed.

Description:
Cute Cottage Appeal
This may be the home you've been waiting for, nestled behind a cottage picket fence and featuring an as new kitchen and bathroom, wide verandah/alfresco area, a large tandem carport and a terrific garage with roller door entry.
Located mid-way between the lovely park and playground and the foreshore board walk, this home has been lovingly maintained by the present owner.
On offer is a 3 bedroom residence with neat cottage gardens, a sheltered undercover alfresco deck off the dining area, a fabulous vegetable patch and a great chicken coop. Your inspection is sure to impress!

Address: CA16 Section A, Coast Road French Island VIC 3921
Description:
COASTAL FRONTAGE
Recently fenced 25 acre coastal allotment with north-facing water views (approx 20 acres inside fence line, of which approx half is usable) with approx 260 meters direct coastal frontage.
Elevated building envelope affording northerly water views by over Western Port Bay and Barrallier Island to Warneet and adjacent to the National Park including the delightful Decoy Lake with its abundant bird life.
Approx 11.5 kms to ferry this property offers natural seclusion and isolation at its best.
Contact Phil Bock on 0438 497 715 for more details and to inspect.

Description:
BLUE RIBBON LAND SITTING IN THE HEART OF CORINELLA
Showcasing an excellent opportunity to purchase a dream parcel of vacant land in this highly sought after pocket of Corinella. This is the ideal blank canvas for a dream home, holiday house, investment or potential development (STCA) The block is approx. 702m. With the possibility of water views from two storey residence.
Only a short walk to the Corinella Beach and Walking Tracks, close to the 24 hour boat jetty, General Store Post Office, close to the Community Centre, Bowls Club, Tennis Courts. You will also be surrounded by all the Bass Coast tourist attractions, Vine Yards, Local Markets, San Remo, Churchill Island Heritage Farm - Philip Island and a lot more.
Once you discover just how dreamy this little town is – You will never want to live anywhere else.
Call Tamara or Daniel today.
